{"id":768730,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lost_Boys","text":"\"The Lost Boys\" is a 1987 American teen horror comedy movie directed by Joel Schumacher. It was produced by Harvey Bernhard with a screenplay written by Jeffrey Boam.\nThe cast includes Corey Haim, Jason Patric, Kiefer Sutherland, Jami Gertz, Corey Feldman, Dianne Wiest, Edward Herrmann, Alex Winter, Jamison Newlander, and Barnard Hughes.\nThe title is a reference to the Lost Boys in J. M. Barrie's stories about Peter Pan and Neverland, who, like the vampires, never grow up.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Teen","surface_form":"teen","offset":35},{"uri":"Horror","surface_form":"horror","offset":40},{"uri":"Comedy","surface_form":"comedy","offset":47},{"uri":"Joel_Schumacher","surface_form":"Joel Schumacher","offset":72},{"uri":"Harvey_Bernhard","surface_form":"Harvey Bernhard","offset":108},{"uri":"Jeffrey_Boam","surface_form":"Jeffrey Boam","offset":153},{"uri":"Corey_Haim","surface_form":"Corey Haim","offset":185},{"uri":"Jason_Patric","surface_form":"Jason Patric","offset":197},{"uri":"Kiefer_Sutherland","surface_form":"Kiefer Sutherland","offset":211},{"uri":"Jami_Gertz","surface_form":"Jami Gertz","offset":230},{"uri":"Corey_Feldman","surface_form":"Corey Feldman","offset":242},{"uri":"Dianne_Wiest","surface_form":"Dianne Wiest","offset":257},{"uri":"Edward_Herrmann","surface_form":"Edward Herrmann","offset":271},{"uri":"Alex_Winter","surface_form":"Alex Winter","offset":288},{"uri":"Jamison_Newlander","surface_form":"Jamison Newlander","offset":301},{"uri":"Barnard_Hughes","surface_form":"Barnard Hughes","offset":324},{"uri":"Lost_Boys_(Peter_Pan)","surface_form":"Lost Boys","offset":372},{"uri":"J._M._Barrie","surface_form":"J. M. Barrie","offset":385},{"uri":"Peter_Pan","surface_form":"Peter Pan","offset":414},{"uri":"Neverland","surface_form":"Neverland","offset":428}]}